60|$|That evening Sophy wrote {{a letter}} to James Fielding saying that she was going away for a time, but imploring him on no account to {{institute}} any inquiry after her, as such a proceeding might damage her to an extent he could not possibly imagine. She told him that she had left Jamie with the Harleys, and recalled his promise that in case of anything happening to her, he would take care of her boy. She inclosed her will appointing him to be her boy's guardian, and her <b>sole</b> <b>executor</b> in case of her death.|$|E
